Note: Our James Beard, author of the popular ‘Fireside Cook Book’, is still in France busily engaged on a writing assignment as well as spending much time learning about the vineyards and restaurants of that country. He will be back in the shop to serve you during the first days of November.

OW back in Paris after several exciting, informative weeks

tasting my way through the wine cellars of Burgundy, Bordeaux, Champagne and Alsace . . . the city now awakening from its August slumber and the signs ‘Fermeture Annuelle’ have been removed ... the incredibly beautiful view of Notre Dame from the Tour d’Argent in the daytime (incidentally, Notre Dame is once again illuminated at night) ... the new smart bar of Claude Terrail of the Tour d’Argent, which is now open opposite the George V. A pleasant spot for a drink or light luncheon lunching with Victor Lanson and Jack Aaron and tasting the really fine Lanson 1945 at the Coq Hardy, which still remains one of the more fabulous country spots outside of Paris Duc de Montesquiou proudly showing me the truly beautiful antique glass Decanter which will house his fine 23 Year Old Armagnac. Sherry’s will have this in time for Christmas . drinking the Royal Chadron Brut 1943 at two large parties and being proud of the fine reception this wine received (you will find it at the Madison Avenue shop for only 3.89 the bottle)
